<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Miserable" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Miserable,</orth> 1) unhappy, wretched: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 1, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 1, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.28" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.234" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 234</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.133" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.351" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 351</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.178" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 178</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.201" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 201</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.85" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.5.88" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.258" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 258</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.4.105" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.1.76" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 3, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.5.44" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.248" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 248</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.248" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 248</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.15.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 15, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 6</bibl>.<lb />2) worthless, despicable, wretched: <cit><quote>a m. world,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.13" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 13</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>O m. age,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 11</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>gross and m. ignorance,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 11</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>O m. thought,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.151" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 151</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>we worldly men have m., mad, mistaking eyes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 66</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what m. praise hast thou for her,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.140" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 140</bibl></cit>. Quibbling in <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.249" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 249</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>